column2: 1) Are you proud of the work that you are doing within your organization?
column3: 2) Is it common for shifting priorities to cause rework or waste in your company?
column4: 3) How honest is the dialogue between employees and managers on your team?
column5: 4) How important are visible figures, metrics, and quantitative objectives to your startup?
column6: 5) Does leadership consistently work toward a common goal of improving the product or service?
column7: 6) How significant are barriers between teams within your company?
column8: 7) How often does leadership make short term decisions that are contrary to the long term vision?
column9: 8) How stable is the number of employees at your company?
column10: 9) How likely are you to look for another job outside of your current company?
column11: 10) How happy are customers with your product or service?
column12: 11) What is your main role in the organization?
column13: 11) What is your main role in the organization? [other]
column14: 12) Are you a member of the leadership team?
column15: 13) How many people work at your company?
column16: 14) How many employees do you manage directly?
